{{Documentation subpage}}

==Usage==

===Opening a single subsection===
{{collapsible sections option
|list= {{hlist |building |civility |notability |humour}}
|default=
|example=}}

Example of the syntax to show (uncollapse) any of the subsections:

* {{tnull|Wikipedia essays|building}}
* {{tnull|Wikipedia essays|civility}}
* {{tnull|Wikipedia essays|notability}}
* {{tnull|Wikipedia essays|humour}}

For example, {{tnull|Wikipedia essays|notability}} will produce:
{{Wikipedia essays|notability}}

===Opening multiple subsections===
To show multiple, or all of, the subsections at once, use state<sub>{{var|n}}</sub>, e.g.:

* {{tnull|Wikipedia essays|state{{=}}expanded|state1{{=}}collapsed|state2{{=}}collapsed|state3{{=}}expanded|state4{{=}}collapsed|state5{{=}}collapsed}}

Parameter <code>state</code> controls the entire template; <code>state1</code> controls the building essays; <code>state2</code> controls the civility essays; <code>state3</code> controls the notability essays; <code>state4</code> controls the humour essays; <code>state5</code> controls the 'About essays' section. These can be set to <code>expanded</code> or <code>collapsed</code>. The above example will produce this:

{{Wikipedia essays|state=expanded|state1=collapsed|state2=collapsed|state3=expanded|state4=collapsed|state5=collapsed}}

==Background==
This template combines the content of the 4 separate templates into one location, for easier watchlisting / updating / organizing / non-duplication / discovery:
* {{tl|Essays on building Wikipedia}}
* {{tl|Civility}}
* {{tl|Essays on notability}} 
* {{tl|Humorous essays}}
* {{tl|User essays}}

It was initially suggested and developed at [[Wikipedia talk:WikiProject Essays#Navbox separation or cohesion|Wikipedia talk:WikiProject Essays §&nbsp;Navbox separation or cohesion]].

